    "Magnitude suppression and direction change (decorrelation) are two key sources of nonlinearity underlying bimanual movements.",
    "We found reduced left hand tuning strength during bimanual movement, resulting in weaker left hand decoding performance (Supplementary Fig. 2b, c).",
    "Reduced left hand tuning is consistent with prior reports of weaker neural representation for the ipsilateral effector during simultaneous movement with a contralateral effector 21, 24, 25, 27, 29, 53.",
    "One way in which this issue may be addressed is with over both hemispheres 21, 23, [54] [55] [56].",
    "Continuous bimanual movement representation across hemispheres remains to be explored and can elucidate the extent to which each hemisphere contributes to the control of its respective effector."
